licant></us-applicants><inventors><inventor sequence="00" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>Carruthers</last-name><first-name>David</first-name><address><city>Livingston</city><country>GB</country></address></addressbook></inventor><inventor sequence="01" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>Di Rollo</last-name><first-name>Ernie</first-name><address><city>Livingston</city><country>GB</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A vehicle load sensing system, said system comprising: at least one load sensor located on a vehicle; display means located on the vehicle; wherein the at least one load sensor is capable of measuring and/or monitoring the load being carried in the vehicle and displaying the measured/monitored level on the display means. The display means may further be a standard mobile phone that has a suitable wireless connection. The information transmitted to the display means may also be transmitted to a further information point allowing a central control of a number of vehicles.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>